-- Argentine Stocks: Grupo Financiero Galicia, Siderar, Tenaris
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-19T21:06:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/argentine-stocks-grupo-financiero-galicia-siderar-tenaris.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 0.7 percent to 2,882.14.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL AF) advanced 1.9 percent
to 3.72 pesos, its fourth consecutive day of gains. Argentina’s
largest consumer lender was the most active stock by value, with
11.8 million pesos ($2.7 million) changing hands. It rose in
line with global markets as jobless claims in the U.S. slid and
as French and Spanish borrowing costs fell.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)   dropped 1.2 percent to 25.1 pesos.
Argentina’s largest steel producer plans to invest $350 million
in 2012 and 2013, according to a statement posted today on the
website of the Buenos Aires stock exchange.  Tenaris SA (TEN)   gained 0.4 percent to 94.15 pesos, its
fourth day of gains. The world’s largest producer of seamless
steel tubes used in the oil industry increased its offer to buy
out minority shareholders in  Brazil ’s Confab Industrial SA by 13
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
